Data Collection

Cinemind does not require users to create an account and does not directly collect personally identifiable information such as name, email address, or phone number.

Movies, series, ratings, notes, and watchlist data created by the user are stored locally on the user’s device and are not uploaded to our servers.

However, the app uses third-party services that may collect certain device-level information.

⸻

Third-Party Services (Advertising)

Cinemind displays banner and interstitial advertisements using Google AdMob, a third-party advertising service.

AdMob may collect the following data automatically:
	•	Device identifiers (such as the advertising identifier)
	•	Approximate usage and interaction data related to ads

This data may be used by Google for:
	•	Displaying ads
	•	Measuring ad performance
	•	Fraud prevention and security

Cinemind does not have access to or control over the data collected by Google AdMob.

Users can remove all ads permanently by purchasing the “Remove Ads” in-app purchase.

⸻

Data Usage

Collected data is used only to:
	•	Display advertisements
	•	Measure advertising performance
	•	Manage in-app features such as the watchlist and personal statistics
	•	Provide a daily AI-powered recommendation based on in-app preferences

⸻

AI Feature

The AI-powered recommendation feature provides one daily suggestion based solely on in-app preferences and interactions.
	•	No personally identifiable information is stored
	•	No personal data is shared with third parties for AI processing
	•	AI recommendations do not involve external user profiling

⸻

Data Sharing

Cinemind:
	•	Does not sell user data
	•	Does not share personal user data with third parties for marketing purposes

Limited data may be shared automatically with third-party services (such as Google AdMob) only for advertising and analytics purposes, in accordance with their privacy policies.

⸻

App Tracking Transparency

Cinemind complies with Apple’s App Tracking Transparency framework.

If required, users are asked for permission before any tracking-related data is accessed. Users can choose whether to allow or deny tracking at any time through their device settings.

⸻

Data Security

All user-generated content (watchlists, ratings, notes) is stored locally on the device.

Reasonable technical and organizational measures are taken to protect user data and ensure app security.

⸻

Children’s Privacy

Cinemind does not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13.

If you believe that a child has provided personal information, please contact us so we can take appropriate action.

⸻

Changes to This Privacy Policy

This privacy policy may be updated from time to time.
Any changes will be reflected within the app or on the App Store product page.

⸻

